text:

Tom Brady celebrated the Patriots' win during the team's parade in Boston. (Photo: Screenshot) 
Tom Brady won his fifth Super Bowl on Sunday night, and he spent the entirety of Monday and Tuesday celebrating. It culminated in downtown Boston on Tuesday, when the entire team took an open-top bus parade through the city with the trophy in tow. 
It was all rather fun. Brady's son unleashed an A+ dab. Tom Brady's son is lit. pic.twitter.com/EWlKqmDzjb — David Heim (@davidheim12) February 7, 2017 
He exchanged a pass with a WBZ host. — Joe Giza (@JoeGiza) February 7, 2017 
Then, best of all, he gave the internet a fun new GIF (although the jury's out on what he could possibly be saying…) OH YEAH **** YEAH pic.twitter.com/uum3cbhB3N — SB Nation GIF (@SBNationGIF) February 7, 2017
